SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DELTA DEVELOPMENT AND HOLY FAMILY ARE EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE, THEREFORE, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES RELATED TO THESE ENTITIES IS REFLECTED IN THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. NEOPOLIS IS A FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION AND IS LIABLE FOR FEDERAL AND NEW YORK STATE INCOME TAXES. CLAIRE COURT IS A LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY AND ITS PROFIT AND LOSS IS REQUIRED TO BE REPORTED BY ITS SOLE MEMBER. ST. PATRICK VILLAGE LLC HAS ELECTED TO BE DISREGARDED AS A SEPARATE ENTITY FOR INCOME TAX PURPOSES. ST. PATRICK VILLAGE LLC'S ACTIVITIES ARE REPORTED ON THE INFORMATIONAL TAX RETURN OF DELTA DEVELOPMENT. THE CORPORATION DISCLOSES OR RECOGNIZES INCOME TAX POSITIONS BASED ON MANAGEMENT'S ESTIMATE OF WHETHER IT IS REASONABLY POSSIBLE OR PROBABLE THAT A LIABILITY HAS BEEN INCURRED FOR UNRECOGNIZED INCOME TAXES. MANAGEMENT HAS CONCLUDED THAT THE CORPORATION HAS TAKEN NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT REQUIRE ADJUSTMENT IN ITS CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.
